### 2. **The Reading Room** *(Old Library / Gentleman's Club)*
Dark forest green backgrounds, ivory text, gold accents. Feels like a private Victorian reading room. Candlelight aesthetic. Unforgettable detail: a single candle flame animation at the top of every article.

---

### 3. **Pub Notebook** *(Irish Pub Study — your original idea)*
British racing green header, cream paper body, leather brown accents, gold dividers. Feels like scribbled notes from a quiet corner booth after midnight. Unforgettable detail: slight paper texture, as if the page is actual notebook paper.

---

### 4. **The Field Dispatch** *(Explorer's Journal)*
Parchment background, brown leather, ink-black type, drop-cap letters, dotted "map path" dividers. Like a 19th-century expedition notebook. Unforgettable detail: a faint compass rose watermark behind each article.

---

### 5. **Regatta** *(Yacht Club Classic)*
Navy + white + regatta red stripes. Clean, crisp, New England coastal. Horizontal stripe dividers, elegant small caps, photography-forward. Unforgettable detail: articles labeled as "Editions" like a sailing club newsletter.

---

### 6. **Via Como** *(Lake Como Summer)*
The lightest, airiest option. Villa cream, terracotta accents, lake blue, olive green. European summer travel diary energy. Unforgettable detail: full-bleed watercolor-wash headers on each article.

---

### 7. **The Gilt Press** *(Editorial Magazine)*
Bold, structured, high-end print magazine feel. Black + gold + cream. Large serif display headlines, strong typographic hierarchy, featured essays. Unforgettable detail: a hand-lettered masthead at the top of every page.

---

### 8. **Mahogany & Brass** *(Golden Age Seafarer)*
Deep sea green + brass gold + aged paper. Antique navigation chart textures, brass-toned accents, compass rose section dividers. Unforgettable detail: background has a very subtle, faded nautical map texture.

---

### 9. **White Sail** *(Minimal Literary)*
The most restrained. Pure cream, single serif typeface, narrow reading column, almost no UI. Like a beautifully typeset novella on screen. Unforgettable detail: a single thin gold rule above the title — nothing else.

---

### 10. **The Correspondent** *(Traveling Writer's Notebook)*
Blends Explorer + Nautical + Italian Summer. Feels like dispatches filed from different cities — Rome, Dublin, the North Sea. Rotating subtle header textures by category. Unforgettable detail: each post has a dateline like a newspaper foreign correspondent — *"Dublin — March 10, 2026"*

